<heading id="894481FBFFDBFFF7A1EA7E1192AA0F15" box="[227,714,1355,1380]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" reason="8">
FAMILY 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFDBFFF7A0367E1192AA0F15" authority="THIELE, 1920" authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1920" box="[319,714,1355,1380]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Psychroteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
PSYCHROTEUTHIDAE 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFDBFFF7A3397E1192AA0F15" author="Thiele J" box="[560,714,1355,1380]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" pagination="433 - 465" refId="ref17394" refString="Thiele J. 1920. Cephalopoden der deutschen Sudpolar- Expedition 1901 - 1903. Zoology 16: 433 - 465." type="journal article" year="1920">THIELE, 1920</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFDBFFF7A08D7E2892490FFA" blockId="18.[388,553,1394,1419]" box="[388,553,1394,1419]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230">(ONE SPECIES)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFDBFFF7A1AA7EC195470A88" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFDBFFF7A1AA7EC192070D70" blockId="18.[163,779,1434,1794]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFDBFFF7A1AA7EC191420FC1" box="[163,290,1435,1456]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Large adult-sized muscular 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFDBFFF7A3847EC0936A0FC1" authorityName="D' ORBIGNY" authorityYear="1845" box="[653,778,1434,1456]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" phylum="Mollusca" rank="order">Oegopsida</taxonomicName>
with buccal connectives attached to the dorsal borders of ventral arms; with two series of arm suckers; tentacles characteristic, with expanded clubs having non-uniform series of suckers, with large suckers with stalks devoid of neck constrictions; carpal locking apparatus in linear series; funnel–mantle locking apparatus straight, reaching the anterior margins of the mantle; glandular structures (possibly photophores) present on the tips of the ventrolateral arms in males and the dorsolateral and ventrolateral arms in females; gladius without conus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFDBFFF7A1AA7C7095470A88" blockId="18.[163,778,1834,1918]" lastBlockId="18.[827,1443,197,250]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFDBFFF7A1AA7C7091700D4E" box="[163,272,1834,1855]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230">Remarks:</emphasis>
Not included in our phylogenetic analyses, but its position as sister group of 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFDBFFF7A33C7C13928F0D2E" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1881" box="[565,751,1865,1887]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Histioteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Histioteuthidae</taxonomicName>
is supported provisionally by its morphology (
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFDBFFF7A3AF7C32936A0D0C" author="Young RE &amp; Vecchione M" box="[678,778,1896,1917]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" refId="ref18209" refString="Young RE, Vecchione M. 2016 a. Histioteuthid families. Version 29 August 2016 (under construction). Available at: http: // tolweb. org / Histioteuthid _ families / 19415 / 2016.08.29" type="url" year="2016">Young &amp;</bibRefCitation>
Vecchione, 2016a) and by the phylogenetic results of 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFDBFFF7A2327BBE93910A8B" author="Lindgren AR" box="[827,1009,228,250]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" pagination="77 - 90" refId="ref15706" refString="Lindgren AR. 2010. Molecular inference of phylogenetic relationships among Decapodiformes (Mollusca: Cephalopoda) with special focus on the squid Order Oegopsida. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 56: 77 - 90." type="journal article" year="2010">Lindgren (2010)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFDBFFF7A5227BBE95400A8B" author="Lindgren AR &amp; Pankey MS &amp; Hochberg FG &amp; Oakley TH" box="[1067,1312,228,250]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230" pagination="129" refId="ref15774" refString="Lindgren AR, Pankey MS, Hochberg FG, Oakley TH. 2012. A multi-gene phylogeny of Cephalopoda supports convergent morphological evolution in association with multiple habitat shifts in the marine environment. BMC Evolutionary Biology 12: 129." type="journal article" year="2012">
Lindgren 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFDBFFF7A5937BBE94B20A88" box="[1178,1234,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1230">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
